<!--
	You can create your own craft recipes on the server using this file.

	SPECIFICATION:
		Recipes: list of recipes
			Recipe: each individual recipe
				displayName: (required) The name of the recipe that will be displayed in the game. It is allowed to
use localization tags defined in your `stringtable.csv`.
				enabled: (required) Determines whether this recipe is enabled on the server. (0 - disabled, 1 -
enabled)
				time: (optional) Determines the time in seconds (floating number) required for the player to make
this recipe . Use -1 for instant recipe.
				
				FirstIngredient and SecondIngredient: (required) ingredient of the craft
					singleUse: (optional) Determines whether the ingredient will be deleted after the end of the craft
(0 - no, 1 - yes)
					minQuantity: (optional) The minimum amount of the quantity needed to start crafting. Floating
number equal or greater then 0. Use -1 to disable the check.
					maxQuantity: (optional) The maximum possbile amount of the quantity to start crafting. Floating
number equal or greater then 0. Use -1 to disable the check.
					minDamage: (optional) The minimum damage of the ingredient needed to start crafting. Where 0 is
pristine, 1 is worn, 2 is damaged, 3 is badly damaged, 4 is ruined.
					maxDamage: (optional) The maximum possbile damage of the ingredient to start crafting. Where 0 is
pristine, 1 is worn, 2 is damaged, 3 is badly damaged, 4 is ruined.
					addHealth: (optional) Determines how much health will be added to the ingredient after the crafting
is complete. Can be used to repair items if `DeleteRequired` is turned off. Value equal or greater
then 0.
					setHealth: (optional) Determines how much health will be set to the ingredient after the crafting
is complete. Can be used to repair items if `DeleteRequired` is turned off. Value equal or greater
then 0. Use -1 to disable this behaviour.
					addQuantity: (optional) Determines how many units of quantity will be added to the ingredient after
crafting is completed. Can be used to repair items if `DeleteRequired` is turned off. Value equal or
greater then 0.
						
						Item: (required) Each possbile ingredient classnames. It is allowed to use base classnames when
needed.
					
					
				CraftingResults: (optional) List with crafting results.
					Result: (required) Each individual crafting result with classname value of resulted item to be
spawned.
						setFullQuantity: (optional) Use 1 to set full quantity or 0 to do nothing.
						setQuantity: (optional) Sets the specific quantity for the resulted item. Floating number equal or
greater then 0. Use -1 to disable this behaviour.
						setHealth: (optional) Sets the specific number of health for the resulted item. Floating number
equal or greater then 0. Use -1 to disable this behaviour.
						inheritsHealth: (optional) Sets the specific behaviour for resulted items health. Use -1 to do
nothing. Use -2 to this result will inherit health from all ingredients averaged. Or use 0 (first
ingredient) or 1 (second ingredient) to this result will inherit health from the specific
ingredient.
						inheritsColor: (optional) Sets the specific behaviour for resulted items color. Use -1 to do
nothing. Or use 0 (first ingredient) or 1 (second ingredient) to composite result classname for this
result item and config value 'color' of ingredient.
						spawnMode: (optional) Sets the specific behaviour to determine spawning position for the resulting
item. Use -2 to spawn result on the ground (default value). Use -1 to place anywhere in the players
inventory. Or use 0 (first ingredient) or 1 (second ingredient) to switch position with specific
ingredient.
				
				
				Conditions: (optional) - list of conditions under which the recipe will be available to the player
					ALL SUPPORTED CONDITIONS YOU CAN FOUND HERE:
https://github.com/TerjeBruoygard/TerjeModsScripting/blob/master/Wiki/en/Conditions/README.md
-->
<Recipes>
	<Recipe displayName="Improvised sewing kit" enabled="1" time="1">
		<FirstIngredient singleUse="1" maxDamage="3">
			<Item>rag_baseitems_sewing_needle</Item>
		</FirstIngredient>
		<SecondIngredient singleUse="1" maxDamage="3">
